glog
------------------------------------------
The glog library implements application-level logging. This library provides
logging APIs based on C++-style streams and various helper macros.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.8.2-1
  libgcc1-5.4.0-1
  libgflags2.2-2.2.1-1bl1
  libglog-devel-0.3.5-1bl1
  libglog0-0.3.5-1bl1
  libstdc++6-5.4.0-1
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-4
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.24.1-1
  gcc-core-5.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-5.4.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-4
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/google/glog

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/google/glog/archive/v0.3.5.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack glog-0.3.5-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./glog-0.3.5-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/glog-0.3.5-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/glog-0.3.5-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libglog0-0.3.5-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libglog-devel-0.3.5-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(glog)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/glog.README
  /usr/share/doc/glog/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/glog/CONTRIBUTORS
  /usr/share/doc/glog/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/glog/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/glog/INSTALL
  /usr/share/doc/glog/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/glog/README
  /usr/share/doc/glog/README.windows
  /usr/share/doc/glog/designstyle.css
  /usr/share/doc/glog/glog.html

(libglog0)
  /usr/bin/cygglog-0.dll

(libglog-devel)
  /usr/include/glog/log_severity.h
  /usr/include/glog/logging.h
  /usr/include/glog/raw_logging.h
  /usr/include/glog/stl_logging.h
  /usr/include/glog/vlog_is_on.h
  /usr/lib/libglog.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libglog.pc

